                as they are fairly common forms. Note that these forms also end in <strong>-e</strong> (<em>sie</em> and <em>wære</em>) and <strong>-en</strong> 
                (<em>sien</em> and <em>wæren</em>) like other subjunctives, so should be easy to spot.
